<subSubSection id="FEB4EF82FF83FFD9FF57FAF3AFC3F8D3" pageId="13" pageNumber="329" type="description">
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF83FFD9FF57FAF3AFF2FA93" blockId="13.[151,1436,1290,2002]" box="[151,493,1290,1315]" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">
Female. Body length: 
<quantity id="715611ECFF83FFD9FE50FAF2AFF6FA93" box="[400,489,1291,1315]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="13" pageNumber="329" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF83FFD9FF07FAD7AF6CFA3E" blockId="13.[151,1436,1290,2002]" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF83FFD9FF07FAD7AF00FAF7" box="[199,287,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">Colour:</emphasis>
vertex brown with face and outline of the eyes yellow, palpi yellow, scape brown, flagellum brown, mesoscutum dark brown to black; metasoma brown, with terga IV–VII lighter; wing veins including stigma light brown; legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF83FFD9FF07FA63AAD7FA66" blockId="13.[151,1436,1290,2002]" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF83FFD9FF07FA63AF1BFA03" box="[199,260,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">Head</emphasis>
: vertex, frons smooth, face granulose; malar space greater than ¼ eye height; temple broad, width equal to ½ eye width; ocell-ocular distance 2.5 times the diameter of lateral ocellus; 23 flagellomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF83FFD9FF07FA1AAC9EF962" blockId="13.[151,1436,1290,2002]" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF83FFD9FF07FA1AAF20FA4B" box="[199,319,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="71AEC78AFF83FFD9FE93FA1BAFFBFA4A" box="[339,484,1506,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
granulose, precoxal sulcus smooth, shorter than width of 
<taxonomicName id="71AEC78AFF83FFD9FB59FA1BAB32FA4A" box="[1177,1325,1506,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Heterospilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesopleuron">mesopleuron</taxonomicName>
; lobes of mesoscutum granulose and hairy just along notauli; notauli scrobiculate meeting before prescutellar furrow in triangular costate area; prescutellar furrow with one cross carina; scutellum granulose; propodeum with basal median areas distinct and margined, basal median areas granulose, basal median carina present, areolar margin indistinct, areolar area rugose, lateral areas entirely rugose, mesosternum granulose. 
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF83FFD9FB8CF98AAAA0F93B" box="[1100,1215,1651,1674]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">Fore wing</emphasis>
: vein r shorter than vein 3 
<collectingCountry id="CEB9FC99FF83FFD9FF1CF96EAF10F91E" box="[220,271,1687,1711]" name="South Africa" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">RSa</collectingCountry>
, vein 1cu-a interstitial with vein 1M, stigma wider to length of vein r. 
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF83FFD9FBF5F96FAAA9F91F" box="[1077,1206,1686,1710]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">Hind wing:</emphasis>
vein SC+R present, length of vein M+CU shorter than vein 
<specimenCount id="A0A87780FF83FFD9FD93F942AC9EF962" box="[595,641,1723,1747]" pageId="13" pageNumber="329" type="generic">1M.</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B611BC09FF83FFD9FF07F926AFC3F8D3" blockId="13.[151,1436,1290,2002]" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis id="84DA601BFF83FFD9FF07F926AF5AF947" box="[199,325,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="329">Metasoma:</emphasis>
first tergum longitudinally costate, apical width equal to length; second tergum longitudinally costate, apical width four to five times the length; tergum III basally costate with apex smooth; terga II+III with anterior transverse groove present and sinuose, posterior transverse groove absent; terga IV–VII smooth; ovipositor equal to length of metasoma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
